ory.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20know%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20study%20in%20college.%20My%20GCE%20A%20Level%20subjects%20in%20high%20school%20were%20mathematics%2C%20history%2C%20and%20English%20literature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20I%20thought%20I%20would%20major%20in%20English%20literature%20because%20the%20subject%20felt%20easy.%20I%20didn't%20really%20have%20to%20study%20for%20it.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20just%20reading%20stories%20and%20could%20get%20A's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20the%20advice%20of%20my%20school's%20career%20advisors%2C%20who%20said%20that%20people%20with%20my%20subject%20combination%20would%20usually%20study%20law.%20They%20told%20me%20law%20was%20a%20prestigious%20field%20that%20offered%20flexibility%20as%20well.%20You%20could%20pivot%20to%20something%20else%20if%20you%20didn't%20like%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20why%20not%20just%20give%20it%20a%20go%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWorking%20as%20a%20lawyer%20was%20exciting%20at%20first%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20at%20an%20international%20law%20firm%20after%20graduating%20from%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20with%20my%20law%20degree.%20I%20was%20based%20in%20the%20firm's%20Malaysian%20office%2C%20focusing%20on%20intellectual%20property%20litigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20enjoyed%20the%20work%20that%20I%20got%20to%20do.%20Although%20what%20I%20studied%20in%20school%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20job%2C%20I%20could%20see%20the%20practical%20impacts%20of%20our%20work.%20I%20got%20to%20jump%20on%20client%20calls%20and%20work%20directly%20with%20senior%20colleagues%20and%20law%20firm%20partners.%20I%20was%20given%20a%20lot%20of%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBut%20the%20lifestyle%20wasn't%20something%20I%20wanted%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20discomfort%20with%20the%20job%20grew%20after%20I%20better%20understood%20the%20nature%20of%20legal%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20as%20a%20litigator%2