0I%20got%20to%20work%20on%20the%20company's%20rebranding%20efforts%20and%20participate%20in%20leadership%20conferences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20doing%20so%20many%20different%20things%20in%20this%20new%20role%2C%20and%20that's%20when%20it%20became%20clear%20to%20me%3A%20The%20law%20wasn't%20something%20I%20enjoyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20struggled%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20this%20because%20I%20didn't%20know%20what%20else%20was%20out%20there%20apart%20from%20the%20law.%20I%20didn't%20have%20an%20answer%20to%20that%20question.%20It%20was%20like%20a%20blank%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20my%20friends%20and%20colleagues%20were%20lawyers.%20There%20didn't%20seem%20to%20be%20an%20alternative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EListening%20to%20podcasts%20changed%20my%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221830%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ling%20Yah%20Wong.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a0ff0843bb77284b9c8a21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221030%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWong%20started%20her%20podcast%20%26quot%3BSo%20This%20Is%20My%20Why%26quot%3B%20in%20June%202020.%3Cp%3ELing%20Yah%20Wong%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20I%20needed%20to%20put%20myself%20out%20there%20and%20gain%20new%20skills.%20I%20didn't%20know%20exactly%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%2C%20but%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20create%20something%20personal%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20I%20discovered%20podcasts.%20I%20remembered%20listening%20to%20a%20podcast%2C%20and%20realizing%20that%20two%20strangers%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20world%20felt%20like%20my%20best%20friends%20after%20that%20episode.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20opened%20my%20mind.%20If%20they%20could%20do%20it%2C%20surely%20I%20could%20do%20so.%20I%20decided%20to%20launch%20my%20podcast%20then.%20I%20figured%20I%20could%20use%20the%20podcast%20to%20talk%20to%20people%2C%20build%20a%20network%2C%20and%20figure%20out%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20with%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20recording%20in%202020%2C%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20I%20was%20still%20working%20as%20an%20in-house%20counsel%20but%20had%20a%20lot%20more%20time%20since%20I%20got%20to%20work%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoing%20the%20podcast%20was%20essentially%20like%20a%20second%20job.%20I%20would%20jump%20into%20podcasting%20after%20each%20workday%2C%20working%20on%20it%20until%201%20to%202%20a.m.%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETaking%20the%20plunge%20and%20leaving%20law%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222406%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wong%20(right)%20recording%20a%20podcast%20with%20her%20guest%2C%20Malaysian%20artist%20Red%20Hong%20Yi%20(left).%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a0f5266979d7371822b921%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221304%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWong%20(right)%20recording%20a%20podcast%20with%20her%20guest%2C%20Malaysian%20artist%20Red%20Hong%20Yi%20(left).%3Cp%3ELing%20Yah%20Wong%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20started%20the%20podcast%2C%20I%20already%20knew%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20leave%20my%20job.%20But%20I%20couldn't%20see%20a%20path%20toward%20it%20because%20I%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20monetize%20what%20looked%20like%20a%20hobby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20changed%20after%20I%20started%20marketing%20my%20podcast%20on%20LinkedIn.%20One%20of%20my%20posts%20went%20viral%20and%20got%20almost%20700%2C000%20impressions.%20That%20was%20very%20exciting%2C%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20double%20down%20on%20those%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20people%20started%20noticing%20me%20and%20reaching%20out%20to%20me.%20Clients%20approached%20me%20to%20create%20content%2C%20but%20I%20had%20to%20say%20no%20to%20projects%20because%20I%20was%20still%20a%20lawyer.%20I%20knew%20there%20was%20some%20kind%20of%20potential%20there%2C%20though%2C%20and%20decided%20to%20take%20the%20risk.%20I%20left%20my%20job%20in%20April%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrankly%2C%20I'm%20earning%20so%20much%20more%20now%20than%20I%20ever%20did%20as%20a%20lawyer.%20If%20anything%2C%20the%20past%20year%20has%20taught%20me%20that%20being%20a%20lawyer%20is%20not%20lucrative.%20When%20you%20take%20on%20a%20salaried%20position%2C%20there's%20a%20cap%20on%20your%20pay.%20But%20the%20sky%20is%20the%20limit%20when%20you%20have%20your%20own%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENo%20regrets%20about%20doing%20law%20first%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20no%20regrets%20about%20starting%20as%20a%20lawyer%20first.%20Part%20of%20the%20reason%20my%20clients%20even%20approach%20me%20in%20the%20first%20place%20is%20because%20I%20have%20a%20legal%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wouldn't%20stand%20out%20as%20much%20if%20I%20didn't%20have%20that.%20And%20I%20also%20wouldn't%20have%20as%20clear%20an%20understanding%20and%20insight%20into%20the%20people%20I'm%20working%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20I%20wished%20I%20had%20done%20earlier%20would%20have%20been%20to%20start%20writing%20online.%20You%20have%20no%20idea%20what%20doors%20could%20open%20to%20you%20once%20you%20put%20yourself%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-being-lawyer-to-write-and-record-podcasts-no-regrets-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705189321000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a0e4286979d7371822b6b7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-being-lawyer-to-write-and-record-podcasts-no-regrets-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ling%20Yah%20Wong%2C%2033%2C%20worked%20as%20a%20lawyer%20for%2010%20years%20before%20she%20decided%20to%20quit.%20She's%20now%20a%20personal%20branding%20strategist%2C%20podcaster%2C%20and%20writer.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktan%40businessinsider.com%20(Kwan%20Wei%20Kevin%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-being-lawyer-to-write-and-record-podcasts-no-regrets-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US'%20Private%20Moon%20Lander%20Now%20Headed%20For%20Earth%2C%20Might%20Burn%20Up%20In%20Atmosphere%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20private%20US%20lunar%20lander%20that%20has%20been%20leaking%20fuel%20throughout%20its%20journey%20is%20now%20headed%20for%20Earth%20and%20will%20likely%20burn%20up%20in%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20the%20company%20said%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAstrobotic%20has%20been%20posting%20regular%20updates%20on%20the%20Peregrine%20lander's%20status%20since%20the%20start%20of%20its%20ill-fated%20voyage%2C%20which%20began%20when%20it%20blasted%20off%20on%20a%20brand%20new%20Vulcan%20rocket%20built%20by%20United%20Launch%20Alliance%20on%20January%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20it%20separated%20from%20the%20rocket%2C%20the%20spaceship%20experienced%20an%20onboard%20explosion%20and%20it%20soon%20became%20clear%20it%20would%20not%20make%20a%20soft%20lunar%20touchdown%20because%20of%20the%20amount%20of%20the%20propellant%20it%20was%20losing%20--%20though%20Astrobotic's%20team%20were%20able%20to%20power%20up%20science%20experiments%20they%20were%20carrying%20for%20NASA%20and%20other%20space%20agencies%2C%20and%20gather%20spaceflight%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20latest%20assessment%20now%20shows%20the%20spacecraft%20is%20on%20a%20path%20towards%20Earth%2C%20where%20it%20will%20likely%20burn%20up%20in%20the%20Earth's%20atmosphere%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Pittsburgh-based%20company%20posted%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20team%20is%20currently%20assessing%20options%20and%20we%20will%20update%20as%20soon%20as%20we%20are%20able.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20box-shaped%20robot%20has%20now%20been%20in%20space%20for%20more%20than%20five%20days%20and%20is%20currently%20242%2C000%20miles%20(390%2C000%20kilometers)%20from%20our%20planet%2C%20Astrobotic%20add