3%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20homeless%20encampment%20sits%20in%20front%20of%20a%20city%20water%20and%20power%20building%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20California.%3Cp%3EMario%20Tama%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20weigh%20in%20on%20a%20case%20that%20could%20upend%20homelessness%20policy%20across%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAt%20issue%20is%20whether%20cities%20can%20ban%20homeless%20individuals%20from%20sleeping%20or%20camping%20in%20public%20areas.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20an%20unusual%20twist%2C%20California%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20asked%20the%20conservative-led%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20hear%20the%20case.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20what%20is%20an%20unusual%20situation%2C%20a%20consortium%20of%20liberal%20politicians%20had%20asked%20the%20conservative-leaning%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20overturn%20a%20lower%20court%20ruling%20that%20has%20kept%20them%20from%20sweeping%20public%20homeless%20encampments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fpolitics%2Fstory%2F2024-01-12%2Fsupreme-court-agrees-to-rule-on-homeless-encampments-in-california-and-the-west%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Supreme%20Court%20agreed%20to%20weigh%20in%20on%20the%20issue%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20decision%20that%20was%20backed%20by%20California%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20and%20other%20Democratic%20leaders%20in%20the%20West%20who%20are%20seeking%20more%20latitude%20to%20address%20homeless%20populations%20that%20have%20become%20more%20prevalent%20in%20the%20region%20in%20recent%20years%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fzsfg.ucsf.edu%2Fnews%2Fcalifornia-unhoused-population-grew-more-22000-start-pandemic%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eespecially%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20is%20of%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20cases%20involving%20the%20rights%20of%20homeless%20individuals%20to%20be%20taken%20up%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20recent%20decades%2C%20and%20it%20could%20have%20huge%20ramifications%20on%20the%20processes%20by%20which%20Western%20states%20approach%20the%20ever-present%20homelessness%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20agreed%20to%20reexamine%20the%20case%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.ca9.uscourts.gov%2Fdatastore%2Fopinions%2F2022%2F09%2F28%2F20-35752.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJohnson%20v.%20City%20of%20Grants%20Pass%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20the%20US%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20for%20the%20Ninth%20Circuit%20deemed%20it%20unconstitutional%20for%20cities%20to%20punish%20homeless%20residents%20for%20staying%20on%20public%20property%20if%20they%20lacked%20access%20to%20shelter%20alternatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.supremecourt.gov%2FDocketPDF%2F23%2F23-175%2F292381%2F20231206101030999_No%252023-175%2520Grants%2520Pass%2520v%2520Johnson%2520BIO%2520Final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPer%20court%20filings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Grants%20Pass%20%E2%80%94%20an%20Oregon%20city%20of%20almost%2040%2C000%20residents%20%E2%80%94%20lacks%20a%20homeless%20shelter.%20And%20two%20smaller%20housing%20programs%20in%20the%20city%20only%20%26quot%3Bserve%20only%20a%20small%20fraction%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20homeless%20population.%20In%202013%2C%20the%20plaintiff's%20attorneys%20wrote%20that%20Grants%20Pass%20%26quot%3Bbegan%20aggressively%20enforcing%20a%20set%20of%20ordinances%20that%20make%20it%20unlawful%20to%20sleep%20anywhere%20on%20public%20property%20with%20so%20much%20as%20a%20blanket%20to%20survive%20cold%20nights.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ninth%20Circuit%20ruled%202-1%20that%20the%20Grants%20Pass%20measure%2C%20which%20set%20out%20to%20bar%20individuals%20from%20sleeping%20in%20public%20with%20items%20like%20blankets%20and%20other%20protections%2C%20was%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20Eighth%20Amendment%20which%20prohibits%20%26quot%3Bcruel%20and%20unusual%20punishments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20has%20united%20many%20liberal%20and%20conservative%20politicians%20as%20they've%20asked%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20overturn%20the%20Ninth%20Circuit's%20ruling%20in%20the%20Grants%20Pass%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENewsom%2C%20along%20with%20Democratic%20leaders%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20and%20Honolulu%2C%20now%20find%20themselves%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.goldwaterinstitute.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FCV2022-010439-926-09202023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20same%20side%20as%20Arizona%20Republican%20lawmakers%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20are%20also%20seeking%20to%20tackle%20homelessness%20in%20public%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCalifornia%20has%20invested%20billions%20to%20address%20homelessness%2C%20but%20rulings%20from%20the%20bench%20have%20tied%20the%20hands%20of%20state%20and%20local%20governments%20to%20address%20this%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.ca.gov%2F2024%2F01%2F12%2Fgovernor-newsom-statement-on-u-s-supreme-court-agreeing-to-hear-case-on-homelessness%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENewsom%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Friday%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Supreme%20Court%20can%20now%20correct%20course%20and%20end%20the%20costly%20delays%20from%20lawsuits%20that%20have%20plagued%20our%20efforts%20to%20clear%20encampments%20and%20deliver%20services%20to%20those%20in%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20expected%20to%20hear%20arguments%20in%20April%2C%20with%20a%20decision%20expected%20by%20the%20early%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomeless-encampments-supreme-court-ruling-newsom-california-oregon-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705179927000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a2f579dcdb354a9857758f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22origin