3A%22Washington%20state%20spent%20over%20%24700%2C000%20on%20giant%20boulders%20to%20deter%20homeless%20encampments%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222313%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20bus%20passes%20overhead%20on%20Interstate%205%20in%20Seattle%20as%20a%20shelter%20of%20tents%2C%20tarps%20and%20wood%20sits%20below%20in%20May%202016.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a2d3396979d73718232e6b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20bus%20passes%20overhead%20on%20Interstate%205%20in%20Seattle%20as%20a%20shelter%20of%20tents%2C%20tarps%20and%20wood%20sits%20below%20in%20May%202016.%3Cp%3EElaine%20Thompson%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWashington%20state%20spent%20over%20%24700%2C000%20on%20boulders%20to%20deter%20homeless%20camps%20in%20some%20areas.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20have%20criticized%20the%20spending%20and%20the%20message%20it%20sends%20to%20the%20homeless.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20one%20official%20told%20BI%20the%20state%20first%20offered%20shelter%20to%20the%20homeless%2C%20and%20a%20majority%20accepted%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWashington%20dropped%20a%20hefty%20amount%20of%20taxpayer%20money%20to%20prevent%20homeless%20encampments%20across%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20state%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Espent%20approximately%20%24718%2C000%20on%20large%20boulders%20placed%20along%20areas%20where%20homeless%20people%20had%20previously%20congregated%20and%20camped%2C%20particularly%20near%20busy%20highways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20residents%20appeared%20conflicted%20about%20the%20spending%20and%20the%20message%20it%20sends%20to%20the%20homeless%2C%20with%20one%20resident%20telling%20local%20news%20outlet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fox13seattle.com%2Fvideo%2F1394426%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFox%2013%20Seattle%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20money%20could%20have%20been%20spent%20in%20better%20ways.%20To%20BI%2C%20state%20officials%20emphasized%20the%20resources%20and%20planning%20that%20went%20into%20finding%20better%20solutions%20for%20the%20homeless%20community%20before%20placing%20the%20boulders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20boulders%20were%20placed%2C%20the%20state%20administration%20offered%20shelter%20to%20the%20homeless%2C%20which%20a%20majority%20of%20them%20accepted%2C%20Kris%20Abrudan%2C%20communications%20director%20of%20Washington%20State%20Department%20of%20Transportation%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRocks%20are%20being%20used%20at%20very%20specific%20locations%20to%20prevent%20re-encampment%20and%20that%20use%20is%20quite%20small%20relative%20to%20the%20number%20of%20encampments%20we%20have%20across%20the%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20Abrudan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20state's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fofm.wa.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpublic%2Fbudget%2Fstatebudget%2Fhighlights%2Fbudget24%2F06_Housing_Homelessness_24_Budget-Policy-Highlights-6.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEncampment%20Resolution%20Program%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Boffers%20a%20humane%20approach%20to%20successfully%20resolving%20encampments%2C%26quot%3B%20Abrudan%20said%2C%20adding%20the%20program%20has%20addressed%2033%20encampment%20sites%20across%20the%20state%20thus%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbrudan%20said%20the%20people%20who%20were%20living%20in%20those%20areas%20%26quot%3Bhad%20meaningful%20access%20to%20the%20housing%20and%20services%20they%20need%20to%20stay%20inside%20and%20that%20program%20has%20been%20quite%20successful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20placed%20boulders%20in%20areas%20near%20the%20state%20capital%20of%20Olympia%20and%20along%20Interstate%205.%20Two%20sites%20along%20the%20highway%20were%20once%20home%20to%20over%20200%20people%20living%20a%20short%20distance%20from%20the%20busy%20interstate%2C%20Abrudan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20relocating%20people%20to%20shelters%2C%20the%20state%20emba