ondered%20if%20he%20could%20fill%20the%20shoes%20left%20by%20his%20predecessor%20Steve%20Jobs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20Cook%20has%20made%20his%20mark%20at%20Apple%2C%20overseeing%20the%20launch%20of%20AirPods%2C%20the%20Apple%20Watch%2C%20and%20Apple%20TV%2B.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETim%20Cook%20has%20helped%20Apple%20become%20the%20most%20valuable%20company%20in%20the%20world%2C%20with%20a%20market%20cap%20approaching%20%243%20trillion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20steered%20the%20tech%20giant%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-jobs-death%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeath%20of%20Steve%20Jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20multiple%20product%20launches%2C%20and%20the%20growth%20of%20Apple's%20subscription%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Cook%20is%20globally%20recognized%20today%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20tech%20companies%2C%20he%20came%20from%20a%20modest%20beginning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20was%20born%20in%20Mobile%2C%20Alabama%2C%20in%201960.%20His%20father%2C%20Donald%20Cook%2C%20was%20a%20shipyard%20worker%20and%20his%20mother%2C%20Geraldine%20Cook%2C%20worked%20at%20a%20pharmacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20graduated%20from%20Alabama's%20Auburn%20University%20in%201982%20with%20a%20degree%20in%20industrial%20engineering.%20After%20college%2C%20Cook%20worked%20at%20IBM%20for%2012%20years.%20While%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F12-facts-you-never-knew-about-apple-ceo-tim-cook-2014-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20at%20IBM%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20earned%20an%20MBA%20at%20Duke%20by%20taking%20night%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20was%20misdiagnosed%20with%20multiple%20sclerosis%20in%201996%2C%20an%20experience%20he%20said%20made%20him%20view%20the%20world%20in%20a%20different%20way.%20Since%20then%2C%20he's%20become%20known%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-cook-daily-routine-schedule-apple-ceo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efitness%20buff%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20left%20IBM%20and%20jumped%20into%20a%20COO%20role%20at%20a%20company%20called%20Intelligent%20Electronics.%20He%20eventually%20became%20vice%20president%20of%20corporate%20materials%20at%20Compaq%2C%20then%20one%20of%20the%20hottest%20PC%20manufacturers%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Steve%20Jobs%20had%20just%20come%20into%20power%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-ceo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple's%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20following%20the%20ouster%20of%20Gil%20Amelio.%20Jobs%20had%20the%20tough%20task%20of%20turning%20the%20company%20around%20after%20many%20years%20of%20fading%20relevance.%20He%20went%20looking%20for%20fresh%20blood%20for%20his%20executive%20team.%20Jobs%20approached%20Cook%2C%20identifying%20him%20as%20a%20strong%20prospect%20for%20the%20new%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETim%20Cook%20goes%20to%20Apple%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20signed%20on%20to%20Apple%20in%201998%20as%20SVP%20of%20worldwide%20operations.%20It%20must%20have%20been%20a%20difficult%20decision%20for%20Cook.%20In%201997%2C%20Apple%20was%20an%20industry%20laughingstock%3A%20Michael%20Dell%2C%20one%20of%20Microsoft's%20closest%20partners%2C%20once%20said%20that%20if%20he%20were%20in%20Jobs'%20shoes%2C%20%26quot%3BI'd%20shut%20it%20down%20and%20give%20the%20money%20back%20to%20the%20shareholders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20experiencing%20Jobs'%20biggest%20flop%20first-hand%20just%20a%20few%20years%20later%20probably%20didn't%20make%20the%20transition%20easier%2C%20either%3A%20In%202000%2C%20Apple%20released%20the%20Power%20Mac%20G4%20Cube%2C%20but%20the%20small%20PC%2C%20which%20Cook%20called%20an%20%26quot%3Bengineering%20marvel%2C%26quot%3B%20never%20found%20its%20audience.%20But%20Cook%20said%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-ceo-tim-cook-on-steve-jobs-and-power-mac-g4-cube-2017-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espectacular%20failure%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20taught%20him%20an%20important%20lesson%20in%20humility%20and%20intellectual%20honesty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20another%20thing%20that%20Steve%20taught%20me%2C%20actually%2C%26quot%3B%20Cook%20said%20during%20a%20visit%20to%20Oxford%20University%20in%202017.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20look%20yourself%20in%20the%20mirror%20and%20say%2C%20'I%20was%20wrong%2C%20it's%20not%20right.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Cook's%20biggest%20early%20coups%20was%20closing%20Apple's%20own%20factories%20and%20warehouses%20and%20replacing%20them%20with%20contract%20manufacturers%2C%20meaning%20that%20devices%20could%20be%20made%20in%20larger%20quantities%20and%20get%20delivered%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0In%202005%2C%20Cook%20also%20started%20making%20investments%20that%20would%20lay%20the%20groundwork%20for%20the%20future%20of%20the%20company%2C%20including%20forming%20critical%20deals%20with%20manufacturers%20on%20flash%20memory%2C%20the%20computer-storage%20component%20that%20would%20form%20the%20basis%20for%20the%20iPhone%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-apple-ipads%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EiPad%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Cook's%20prescience%20meant%20that%20when%20competitors%20sought%20to%20build%20their%20own%20phones%20and%20tablets%2C%20they%20had%20to%20compete%20for%20what%20little%20factory%20capacity%20and%20components%20those%20factories%20could%20spare%2C%20after%20they%20had%20already%20fulfilled%20their%20commitments%20to%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20Cook's%20management%20expertise%2C%20his%20star%20within%20the%20company%20rose%20rapidly.%20Apple%20was%20on%20the%20track%20toward%20growth%20and%20big%20profits%2C%20and%20Cook%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20credit.%20As%20his%20influence%20grew%2C%20Cook%20became%20known%20within%20the%20company%20for%20his%20no-mercy%2C%20relentless%20questioning%2