%80%99s%20caption%20read%3A%20%E2%80%98He%20will%20roar%20but%20cannot%20bite.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%201974%2C%20Abdullah%E2%80%99s%20revolutionary%20fervor%20had%20waned%2C%20replaced%20by%20a%20treacherous%20%E2%80%93%20or%2C%20as%20some%20would%20say%2C%20pragmatic%20%E2%80%93%20acceptance%20of%20the%20position%20of%20chief%20minister%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20within%20the%20Indian%20union.%20It%20was%20a%20momentous%20decision%20for%20which%20he%20has%20earned%20revulsion%20from%20Kashmiris%20to%20this%20day%2C%20yet%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20appeared%20to%20be%20an%20inevitable%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20biography%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Lives%3C%2Fem%3E%20series%2C%20%3Cem%3ESheikh%20Abdullah%3A%20The%20Caged%20Lion%20of%20Kashmir%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Chitralekha%20Zutshi%2C%20edited%20by%20Ramachandra%20Guha%2C%20successfully%20captures%20the%20essence%20of%20its%20subject%20and%20presents%20a%20much%20needed%20exploration%20of%20a%20man%20who%20was%20both%20deeply%20admired%20and%20often%20derided.%20A%20guide%20and%20a%20harbinger%20of%20freedom%20to%20some%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%20a%20traitor%2C%20a%20demagogue%20and%20an%20opportunist%20to%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20199px)%2085vw%2C%20199px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13160146%2Fimage-1737-199x300.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22199%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13160146%2Fimage-1737-199x300.png%20199w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13160146%2Fimage-1737.png%20428w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692809%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESheikh%20Abdullah%3A%20The%20Caged%20Lion%20of%20Kashmir%20by%20Chitralekha%20Zutshi%20(Fourth%20Estate%20India%2C%20December%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contemporary%20Kashmir%2C%20inquiring%20about%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%20often%20yields%20acerbic%20responses%20with%20many%20condemning%20him%20for%20selling%20Kashmir%20down%20the%20drain%20in%201975.%20Zutshi%20delves%20into%20this%20problem%20meticulously%20and%20reaches%20an%20interesting%20conclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKashmiris%20born%20prior%20to%201947%20continue%20to%20revere%20Abdullah%20as%20a%20pious%2C%20peerless%20individual.%20However%2C%20the%20generation%20born%20after%201947%20%E2%80%93%20who%20came%20of%20age%20when%20he%20was%20in%20prison%20and%20were%20young%20adults%20at%20the%20time%20of%201975%20Kashmir%20Accord%20%E2%80%93%20are%20particularly%20embittered%20by%20what%20they%20see%20as%20a%20betrayal%20of%20their%20political%20dreams%3B%20dreams%20that%20he%20had%20himself%20fostered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20biography%20of%20the%20series%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FAsoka-History-Historical-Patrick-Olivelle-ebook%2Fdp%2FB08C1QLWSW%5C%22%3Eabout%20Ashoka%2C%20authored%20by%20Patrick%20Ollivelle.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJawaharlal%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20unwavering%20backing%20of%20Abdullah%20in%20his%20struggle%20against%20the%20Dogra%20Raj%20paid%20off%20in%20the%20form%20of%20the%20state%20acceding%20to%20the%20Indian%20union%20in%201947.%20It%20was%20evident%20that%20Nehru%2C%20with%20his%20distinct%20motivations%2C%20strategically%20nurtured%20Abdullah%20as%20a%20counterbalance%20to%20Jinnah%20and%20his%20two-nation%20theory.%20Abdullah%20did%20not%20need%20Nehru%20as%20much%20as%20Nehru%20needed%20him%20at%20this%20point%20of%20time%20in%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20history.%20However%2C%20when%20Abdullah%20began%20to%20outgrow%20his%20assigned%20role%20in%201953%2C%20he%20was%20decisively%20curtailed%20and%20put%20under%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrison%20punctuated%20his%20political%20life%20multiple%20times.%20He%20would%20spend%20a%20total%20of%2016%20years%2C%20six%20months%20and%2022%20days%20in%20jail%20as%20a%20prisoner%20either%20of%20princely%20Dogra%20state%20before%201947%20or%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20state%20within%20Independent%20India%20that%20followed%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1953%20was%20a%20pivotal%20moment%20in%20the%20association%20between%20Kashmir%20and%20India%2C%20altering%20its%20dynamics%20forever.%20The%20escalating%20Praja%20Parishad%20agitation%20in%20Jammu%2C%20spearheaded%20by%20Balraj%20Madhok%2C%20strategically%20aligned%20itself%20with%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%2C%20exerting%20significant%20pressure%20on%20Nehru%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20dismissal%20of%20Abdullah%20in%201953.%20Jammu%20Hindus%20were%20acutely%20unhappy%20with%20the%20economic%20policies%20of%20the%20National%20Conference%2C%20particularly%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20Big%20Landed%20Estates%20Abolition%20Act%20in%20October%201950.%20According%20to%20this%20Act%2C%20the%20maximum%20amount%20of%20land%20that%20a%20landlord%20could%20hold%20was%20182%20kanals%20(22.75%20acres)%20and%20transfer%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20land%20to%20the%20tenants%2C%20who%20had%20until%20that%20point%20worked%20as%20serfs%20on%20the%20land.%20The%20Praja%20Parishad%20felt%20that%20this%20was%20against%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20landlords%20of%20Jammu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20movement%20demanded%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%98Ek%20Vidhan%2C%20Ek%20Pradhan%2C%20Ek%20Nishan%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20(One%20Constitution%2C%20One%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20One%20Flag)%2C%20precisely%20to%20undo%20these%20reforms.%20For%20Sheikh%2C%20India%20meant%20Nehru%2C%20and%20this%20is%20where%20he%20erred.%20His%20friend%2C%20on%20whose%20advice%20he%20had%20once%20converted%20the%20Muslim%20Conference%20into%20the%20National%20Conference%20in%201939%20and%20earned%20the%20wrath%20of%20his%20fellow%20companions%2C%20was%20accusing%20him%20of%20being%20communal%20and%20approved%20of%20his%20arrest%20in%201953.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F08%2FJawaharlal_Nehru_in_conversation_with_Sheikh_Mohd._Abdullah_in_the_Constituent_Assembly.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22729%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F08%2FJawaharlal_Nehru_in_conversation_with_Sheikh_Mohd._Abdullah_in_the_Constituent_Assembly.jpg%20452w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F08%2FJawaharlal_Nehru_in_conversation_with_Sheikh_Mohd._Abdullah_in_the_Constituent_Assembly-263x300.jpg%20263w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-59001%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22831%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJawaharlal%20Nehru%20in%20conversation%20with%20Sheikh%20Mohd.%20Abdullah%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly.%20Credit%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELife%20in%20prison%20and%20sacred%20spaces%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbdullah%E2%80%99s%20enduring%20popularity%20as%20the%20most%20significant%20leader%20of%20Kashmir%20through%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20according%20to%20Zutshi%2C%20is%20best%20understood%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20two%20themes%20that%20defined%20his%20political%20career%3A%20prison%20and%20sacred%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20illustrate%20this%2C%20two%20crucial%20instances%20from%20his%20political%20career%20are%20paramount%20to%20understand.%20In%201953%2C%20Abdullah%E2%80%99s%20administration%20faced%20criticism%20for%20severe%20corruption%20and%20other%20maladies.%20His%20plummeting%20popularity%20was%20instantly%20restored%20as%20soon%20as%20he%20was%20dismissed%20in%201953%20and%20made%20a%20political%20prisoner%20again%2C%20allowing%20him%20to%20reprise%20his%20role%20as%20a%20revolutionary%20leader%20of%20the%20movement%20of%20Kashmiri%20self-determination.%20In%201975%2C%20after%20the%20accord%20with%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20Abdullah%E2%80%99s%20popularity%20in%20Kashmir%20took%20a%20severe%20beating.%20In%20an%20attempt%20to%20salvage%20his%20image%2C%20he%20initiated%20the%20construction%20of%20Hazratbal%20shrine%2C%20aiming%20to%20turn%20around%20the%20public%20opinion%20but%20failed%20to%20do%20so%20substantially.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20would%20not%20allow%20Kashmir%20to%20be%20merged%20into%20and%20fall%20to%20the%20tyranny%20of%20the%20postcolonial%20state%20after%20delivering%20it%20from%20the%20authoritarianism%20of%20princely%20rule.%20And%20yet%20in%20one%20of%20the%20central%20contradictions%20of%20his%20political%20career%2C%20at%20certain%20times%20when%20he%20was%20in%20power%2C%20he%20himself%20became%20the%20postcolonial%20state%E2%80%99s%20most%20trusted%20agent%20and%20the%20repressor%20of%20his%20own%20people%E2%80%99s%20rights.%20His%20image%20as%20a%20Muslim%20leader%20in%20Kashmir%20was%20one%20that%20he%20would%20carefully%20cultivate%20and%20maintain%20even%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20alienating%20people%20from%20Jammu%20and%20Ladakh%20provinces%20of%20the%20state.%20Ideally%2C%20he%20wanted%20to%20be%20both%20a%20Muslim%20leader%20as%20well%20as%20a%20secular%2C%20nationalist%20one%2C%20but%20succeeded%20in%20being%20neither.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20contemporary%20Kashmiri%20psyche%2C%20Abdullah%E2%80%99s%20image%20is%20less%20that%20of%20a%20liberator%20who%20freed%20his%20people%20from%20the%20clutches%20of%20feudalism%20and%20Dogra%20rule%2C%20endowing%20them%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20dignity.%20Instead%2C%20he%20is%20often%20perceived%20as%20a%20figure%20who%20veered%20away%20from%20the%20very%20cause%20of%20Kashmiri%20nationalism%20that%20he%20had%20meticulously%20crafted%20and%20ardently%20fought%20for.%20As%20his%20life%20drew%20to%20a%20close%2C%20the%20spectre%20of%20%E2%80%98Kashmiri%20nationalism%E2%80%99%20haunted%20him.%20He%20was%20called%20a%20Frankenstien%20who%20created%20the%20monster%20of%20%E2%80%98Kashmiri%20nationalism%E2%80%99%20and%20now%20had%20to%20pay%20the%20ultimate%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZutshi%E2%80%99s%20biography%20brings%20to%20the%20table%20an%20array%20of%20arguments%20that%20act%20as%20a%20counterbalance%20to%20this%20dominant%20narrative.%20The%20watershed%20moment%20of%20losing%20East%20Pakistan%20in%20the%201971%20India-Pakistan%20war%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20shaking%20Abdullah%E2%80%99s%20belief%20in%20Pakistan%20being%20a%20potent%20player%20in%20the%20Kashmir%20dispute.%20He%20lamented%20that%20he%20could%20not%20stand%20idly%20by%20witnessing%20the%20gradual%20decline%20of%20his%20beloved%20Kashmir%2C%20plagued%20by%20corruption%2C%20familial%20separations%20across%20borders%2C%20inflation%2C%20and%20unemployment%20among%20the%20educated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMotivated%20by%20a%20profound%20desire%20to%20rectify%20these%20issues%2C%20he%20made%20a%20strategic%20return%20to%20power%20with%20the%20ambitious%20vision%20of%20forging%20a%20New%20Kashmir.%20The%20Kashmiri%20cartoonist%2C%20Bashir%20Ahmad%20Bashir%2C%20captured%20the%20feelings%20of%20the%20people%20at%20this%20time.%20In%20one%20of%20the%20cartoons%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dnaindia.com%2Fanalysis%2Fstandpoint-bashir-ahmad-bashir-the-wizard-of-lines-and-curves-from-kashmir-1988661%5C%22%3Eshowed%3C%2Fa%3E%20Abdullah%20striding%20towards%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20chief%20minister%20while%20a%20grave%20in%20the%20background%20marked%20%E2%80%98Liberation%20Front%E2%80%99%20cries%20out%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EMeri%20Kahani%20bhoolne%20wale%2C%20tera%20jahan%20aabaad%20rahe%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(Oh%20you%2C%20who%20forget%20my%20story%2C%20may%20your%20world%20prosper).%20He%20died%20a%20sad%2C%20broken%20man%2C%20crushed%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20his%20unfulfilled%20promises%20to%20the%20Kashmiri%20people.%20This%20biography%20by%20Zutshi%20is%20as%20much%20a%20biography%20of%20this%20one%20towering%20man%20as%20it%20is%20of%20the%20entire%20generation%20of%20leaders%20who%20shaped%20the%20destiny%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ESaleem%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3ERashid%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EShah%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20a%20book%20critic%20and%20an%20independent%20writer%20based%20in%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705142766000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07143637%2F1024px-Sheikh_Abdullah_addressing_people.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-legacy-of-sheikh-abdullah-amidst-shifting-narratives-in-kashmir%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20second%20biography%20in%20the%20'Indian%20Lives'%20series%2C%20'Sheikh%20Abdullah%3A%20The%20Caged%20Lion%20of%20Kashmir'%20by%20Chitralekha%20Zutshi%2C%20edited%20by%20Ramachandra%20Guha%2C%20successfully%20captures%20the%20essence%20of%20its%20subject%20and%20presents%20a%20much%20needed%20exploration%20of%20a%20man%20who%20was%20both%20deeply%20admired%20and%20often%20derided.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-legacy-of-sheikh-abdullah-amidst-shifting-narratives-in-kashmir%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20proposal%20to%20lift%20export%20curbs%20on%20wheat%2C%20rice%2C%20sugar%2C%20says%20Piyush%20Goyal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705142683000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-06%2F27%2Ffull%2F1687831616-2592.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fagriculture%2Fno-proposal-to-lift-export-curbs-on-wheat-rice-sugar-says-piyush-goyal-124011300309_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20had%20banned%20wheat%20exports%20in%20May%202022%2C%20non-basmati%20rice%20exports%20from%20July%2